diabetes, football and omnipod

   [48]Options
     * Mark as New
     * Bookmark
     * Subscribe to Direct Replies to This Post
     *
     * [49]Subscribe to RSS Feed
     *
     * [50]Highlight
     * [51]Print
     * Email to a Friend
     *
     * [52]Report Inappropriate Content

   07-02-2013 04:56 PM

   My son was diagnosed with type 1 diabeties in May 2010 when he was 9
   years old.   He has used the omnipod since January 2011.  We love the
   freedom and control the tubeless pump gives him.   However, we are
   facing a new set of circumstances with our pump this year as he enters
   7th grade.  He has always been very active and plays many different
   organized sports.  While basketball and baseball have never given us
   any trouble with the omnipod, football has.  In the past, he has just
   played youth league football and the practices were just twice a week.
    He would often knock off the pod during practice or a game, but since
   it wasn't everyday, it wasn't that big of a deal.  As he goes to junior
   high football this fall, he will have practice every day.  We are
   considering going off of the omnipod and back onto shots for football
   season.  I would like to hear from other parents who have children that
   have played football with the omnipod and find out what the experience
   was like.
   [53]Report Inappropriate Content
