   07-03-2013 12:06 PM

   Hi

   I hope your son has a great football season.  My son, now 18, did not
   play football but did play basketball,run track and Varsity Golf with
   the medtronic pump with tubing.  Check with your diabetes team, but
   from what I remember, he checked blood sugar b4 practice or game,
   bolused for half the basal he would miss while pump was disconnected,
   ate a snack with no bolus, and did game/practice disconnected.  He also
   drank gatorade while disconnected.  He has run into trouble after
   practice going low several hours later.  CDE suggested 50% basal rate
   for a few hours after sport.  Even now, he has to be careful when he
   works out.  He disconnects and drinks gatorade without covering the
   carbs.  He also disconnected for pe in high school.  Again, check with
   your endo team or cde as I am pretty removed from the day to day
   management of diabetes any more.  They grow up and that does happen. I
   would not give up the pump if possible.  Junior high is such a changing
   time and the pump gives kids the freedom to eat when they want (which
   is all the time for growing boys) and fit in.  Do not be surprised it
   he eats 4-5 meals a day.  They are hungry and burning through food with
   all the activity.  Take care and let us know how it goes.


   G 18 diagnosed 3/22/08
