   07-15-2013 05:15 PM

   My daughter has worn her Omnipod for soccer, swimming, softball and
   basketball. We use Opsite flexifix tape when we need extra support.
   It's a clear plastic, very thin, tape.( Think of sticky saran wrap.) I
   get the 4 inch wide roll and cut it into 7 strips 4 boxes wide. I place
   a strip on each of the 4 sides, directly on top of the adhesive it
   comes with. the other 3 strips I place across the body of the pod. This
   works well for us. I tried using a single large piece of the tape put
   this didn't work well for us. Also we use the Bands 4 Life arm band
   when it's on her arm. They make versions for the stomach and thigh
   too.  It's a swimsuit like material sewn into a band which you place
   over the pod. This has worked very well as my daughter does not like to
   put the tape on her arms ( pulls the hair there).. My dry cleaner
   tailor lady thought she could make some for us too, so if someone you
   know has some sewing skills you could do yourself.  Maybe a combo of
   both would do the trick! Best of luck.
