   07-16-2013 09:50 PM

   When my son played 6th grade football last year, we had to change the
   pod every day that they were "hitting."  He was on the line, and the
   hittling would dislodge the cannula.  He wore it on his arm instead of
   the leg, and we put in the minium amount of insulin.  They only had
   football 4 days a week for 6 weeks.  We did not go to shots.  He
   suspended the insulin for practices with lots of activity.
